remarks.format: ## Remarks 枚举表示队列的内容的时间在实时快照。The enumeration represents a moment-in-time snapshot of the contents of the queue. 它不反映之后对集合的任何更新调用。It does not reflect any updates to the collection after was called. 枚举数可以安全地从读取一起使用，并将写入队列。The enumerator is safe to use concurrently with reads from and writes to the queue. 枚举器中在其中添加它们，这是先进先出顺序 （先入先出） 的顺序返回集合元素。The enumerator returns the collection elements in the order in which they were added, which is FIFO order (first-in, first-out).

remarks.format: ## Remarks 将内部处理所有同步。 handles all synchronization internally. 如果两个线程正好在同一时间调用 ，则不会阻止任一操作。If two threads call at precisely the same moment, neither operation is blocked. 如果在两个线程之间检测到冲突，则一个线程必须再次尝试检索下一元素，并且将内部处理同步。When a conflict is detected between two threads, one thread has to try again to retrieve the next element, and the synchronization is handled internally. 将尝试从队列中删除元素。 tries to remove an element from the queue. 如果此方法成功，则将删除该项，并且此方法将返回 `true`；否则将返回 `false`。If the method is successful, the item is removed and the method returns `true`; otherwise, it returns `false`. 对于队列中的其他操作而言，这将以原子方式发生。That happens atomically with respect to other operations on the queue. 如果队列是使用代码（如 `q.Enqueue("a"); q.Enqueue("b"); q.Enqueue("c");`）填充的，并且两个线程同时尝试取消元素排队，则一个线程将取消 `a` 排队，而另一个线程将取消 `b` 排队。If the queue was populated with code such as `q.Enqueue("a"); q.Enqueue("b"); q.Enqueue("c");` and two threads concurrently try to dequeue an element, one thread will dequeue `a` and the other thread will dequeue `b`. 对 的两个调用均将返回 `true`，因为它们都能取消元素排队。Both calls to will return `true`, because they were both able to dequeue an element. 如果每个线程都返回取消附加元素排队，则一个线程将取消 `c` 排队并返回 `true`，而另一个线程将发现队列为空并返回 `false`。If each thread goes back to dequeue an additional element, one of the threads will dequeue `c` and return `true`, whereas the other thread will find the queue empty and will return `false`.
